window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>An invitation to a mysterious theatrical performance changes the lives of two women in Adam Rapp’s riveting new audio play <i>The Cube</i>. Magda, an upper-class White woman, is shocked to the core by what she sees—and questions her complicity. Ruth, a Black woman who played a role in the show, is thrilled to be part of it—until she discovers her performance is all too convincing. Directed by Whitney White, a visceral and truly immersive audio experience that tackles issues of race, privilege, and cultural blindness.</p>"; 
